    <string name="token_add_help_title">Import token guide</string>
    <string name="token_add_help_desc">View token import guide</string>
    <string name="token_add_help_intro_label">What this does</string>
    <string name="token_add_help_intro">Enter the contract address of an ERC-20 token deployed on BrokerChain to import it into your wallet. After importing, you can view its balance and history on the Tokens page. Please verify the token source and risks yourself. The wallet does not endorse third-party tokens.</string>
    <string name="token_add_help_format_label">Contract address format</string>
    <string name="token_add_help_format">• The address must start with 0x and be followed by 40 hexadecimal characters (0–9, a–f, case insensitive)\n• Example: 0x1234567890abcdef1234567890abcdef12345678\n• Do not include spaces, line breaks, or other extra characters\n• The address must belong to a token contract on BrokerChain, not a personal wallet address\n• When pasting or scanning, make sure the content is the contract address only. Prefixes such as ethereum: are handled automatically</string>
    <string name="token_add_help_standard_label">Token contract requirements</string>
    <string name="token_add_help_standard">• The contract should implement standard ERC-20 methods, including symbol(), name(), decimals(), balanceOf(), and transfer()\n• On-chain name and symbol values may be stored as either string or bytes32\n• wrapped BKC (wBKC) is built in by default, so its contract address should not be imported again\n• A token that is already in your list cannot be added twice</string>
    <string name="token_add_help_notice_label">Important notes</string>
    <string name="token_add_help_notice">• Anyone can deploy a token contract. Importing a token only adds it to your local wallet view and is not an official endorsement\n• Common import failures include: invalid address, target is not a contract, token metadata cannot be read on-chain, or network issues\n• Do not use the contract address to receive tokens. Always use your wallet address\n• Only enable tokens you trust. You can disable unwanted tokens later in Manage tokens</string>
    <string name="token_send_failure_hint_dash">Check: 1) Device can reach dash.broker-chain.com 2) Correct private key imported 3) Enough BKC for gas</string>
    <string name="token_send_failure_hint_local">Check: BrokerChain node is running and the account is unlocked</string>
    <string name="token_send_failure_hint_network">Check that the network can reach dash.broker-chain.com</string>
